An improv group is something I haven't seen explored in Foundation material before, but you brought it to the next level with an engaging discovery log and exploration of how the group survived before they were contained. I'm a little more neutral on the guard being incorporated into the group, but it's an interesting take on the give and take nature of improv; if the audience isn't willing to give an idea, it has to give something far greater. +1 from me, it's an example of an SCP that presents an interesting story without needing a sense that it's part of something larger.







